  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Deseed your <strong>peppers </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips (as finely as you can)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-and-goats-cheese-tart/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10 min or until the peppers begin to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-and-goats-cheese-tart/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Add the<strong> discs</strong> to a separate baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-and-goats-cheese-tart/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, unroll your <strong>puff pastry</strong> and cut it into 1 square per person</p><p>Transfer the <strong>pastry square[s]</strong> to a sheet of <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong> (the size of a baking tray)</p><p>Score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife and prick the inside of the border all over with a fork (this will stop you getting a soggy bottom!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-and-goats-cheese-tart/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the peppers have softened, remove them from the oven</p><p>Top the centre of the <strong>pastry squares</strong> with the<strong> softened peppers</strong> and transfer them (on the baking paper) to a baking tray</p><p>Tip: Use the same baking tray the peppers were on to save on washing up!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-and-goats-cheese-tart/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the pastry is golden and crisp and the edges have puffed up – these are your <strong>roasted pepper tarts</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-and-goats-cheese-tart/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the roasted pepper tarts are cooking, combine your<strong> cider vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Crumble your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-pepper-and-goats-cheese-tart/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>roasted pepper tarts</strong> with the<strong> crumbled goats' cheese</strong> and season them with <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>roasted pepper & goats' cheese tarts</strong> with the <strong>crispy potatoes</strong> and a handful of <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>dressing</strong> over the salad</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
